    "question_id" : 6094575,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can also invoke methods inside the created object.</p>\n\n<p>You can create object instant by invoking the first constractor and then invoke the first method in the created object. </p>\n\n<pre><code>    Class&lt;?&gt; c = Class.forName(\"mypackage.MyClass\");\n    Constructor&lt;?&gt; ctor = c.getConstructors()[0];\n    Object object=ctor.newInstance(new Object[]{\"ContstractorArgs\"});\n    c.getDeclaredMethods()[0].invoke(object,Object... MethodArgs);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3837510,
      "reputation" : 411,
      "user_id" : 3181500,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4ccd22ccc97e1b8f221a4916caf63213?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
