    "creation_date" : 1483616452,
    "answer_id" : 41484158,
    "question_id" : 6094575,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Another helpful answer. <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/9335669/3181500\">How do I use getConstructor(params).newInstance(args)?</a></p>\n\n<pre><code>return Class.forName(**complete classname**)\n    .getConstructor(**here pass parameters passed in constructor**)\n    .newInstance(**here pass arguments**);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In my case, my class's constructor takes Webdriver as parameter, so used below code:  </p>\n\n<pre><code>return Class.forName(\"com.page.BillablePage\")\n    .getConstructor(WebDriver.class)\n    .newInstance(this.driver);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 3368068,
